pageContext.claim: “So disgraceful that the questions concerning the Russian Witch Hunt were “leaked” to the media. No questions on Collusion. Oh, I see...you have a made up, phony crime, Collusion, that never existed, and an investigation begun with illegally leaked classified information. Nice!”
pageContext.analysis: It is unclear who leaked the questions to The New York Times but it was later determined these were questions assembled by Trump's lawyers based on conversations with the special prosecutor, not questions that the prosecutor had submitted. At least 13 of the questions dealt with collusion.
